About CompScience

At CompScience, we're not just building software—we're saving lives. We're a high-growth startup on a mission to prevent 10 million workplace injuries through bold technological innovations, ensuring that everyone can go home safe at the end of the day.

Founded in 2019 and backed by investors from SpaceX, Tesla, and Anduril, we've assembled a powerhouse team that bridges two worlds:

Cutting-Edge Technology: Our engineering team is comprised of distinguished computer vision engineers, software architects, and data scientists from the self-driving car industry. They bring unparalleled expertise in AI and machine learning to the realm of workplace safety.

Insurance Acumen: Our insurance team comprises seasoned professionals who understand the nuances of workers' compensation policies. They work hand-in-hand with our tech experts to translate advanced analytics into tangible insurance products that truly serve our clients' needs.

Our groundbreaking perception-based risk assessment program, the first of its kind, provides the most comprehensive data stream available for risk analysis and monitoring and has proven to significantly reduce accidents in some of the world's most hazardous occupations.

About the Role

We are looking for a Front-End Engineer to join our development team. This individual will play a critical role in building smooth, modern, and customer-facing applications to fulfill our mission to increase worker safety and save lives. The ideal candidate should be hands-on and proficient in React, Material.io for styling, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS. They should also be familiar with AWS app deployment and have some knowledge of API design and contracts. Experience with code reviews and working with overseas teams is essential.

Responsibilities

Develop and maintain high-quality, responsive, and performant front-end code.

Use React, Material.io, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS to build and style applications.

Participate in the deployment of applications on AWS.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless integration and deployment.

Participate in API design and ensure proper integration of front-end with back-end services.

Conduct code reviews and mentor junior front-end developers.

Ensure cross-browser compatibility and resolve any browser-specific issues.

Stay updated with the latest industry trends and best practices in front-end development.

Required Experience

BSc in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.

3+ years of experience in front-end development.

Proficiency in React, Material.io, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.

Familiarity with AWS app deployment.

Working knowledge of API design and integration.

Familiarity with Figma for UI design is a plus

Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

Strong communication skills and ability to work in a collaborative environment with offshore teams.

